@model Ux.Mvc.ViewModels.Examples
<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Foreign keys <small>string</small></h1>
</div>
<p>If you have foreign keys in your model,...</p>
<p>Requirements:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Map your integer values to strings in your view model. This is required for the selected values.</li>
    <li>Annotate the property in your view model with <code>[UxHint(UxHintType.Select)]</code> to indicate that it should be presented as a select list.</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight">
    <pre class="prettyprint">
[UxHint(UxHintType.Select)]
public string ForeignKeyValue { get; set; }

ForeignKeyValue = ""4""
</pre>
</div>

<h3>Raw</h3>
<div class="example">
    @Model.ForeignKeyValue
</div>
<div class="highlight">
    <pre class="prettyprint">
@@Model.ForeignKeyValue
</pre>
</div>

<h3>DisplayFor</h3>
<div class="example">
    @Html.DisplayFor(m => m.ForeignKeyValue)
</div>
<div class="highlight">
    <pre class="prettyprint">
@@Html.DisplayFor(m => m.ForeignKeyValue)
</pre>
</div>

<h3>EditorFor<small>Select.cshtml</small></h3>
<p>There are many overloads for the <code>EditorFor</code> helper. To pass a datasource through to the editor for a foreign key, use the <code>UxEditorFor</code> helper instead.</p>
<div class="example">

    @Html.UxEditorFor(m => m.ForeignKeyValue, @Model.DataSources["ungrouped"])
</div>
<div class="highlight">
    <pre class="prettyprint">
@@Html.UxEditorFor(m => m.ForeignKeyValue)
</pre>

</div>

